Module org.microbean.type
Package org.microbean.type

Class JavaType

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.type.Type<Type>
org.microbean.type.JavaType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Owner<Type>
@Experimental public class JavaType extends Type<Type>
A Type that models a java.lang.reflect.Type for use primarily by a Type.Semantics instance.
Author:
Laird Nelson

  • Constructor Details

    • JavaType

      protected JavaType(boolean box, Type type)
      Creates a new JavaType.
      Parameters:
      box - whether boxing of primitive types will be in effect; even if true boxing only happens to primitive types
      type - the Java Type being modeled; must not be null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if type is null

    • JavaType

      protected JavaType(boolean box, List<?> supertypes)
      Creates a new JavaType that models custom supertypes.

      Among other things, this means that the Type.object() method will return null.

      Parameters:
      box - whether boxing of primitive types will be in effect; even if true boxing only happens to primitive types
      supertypes - a List of supertypes; must not be null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if supertypes is null
